Your ML service uses a Logistic Regression algorithm for classification.

Specifically, looking at the train_model.py file, it uses LogisticRegression from the scikit-learn library.

Before the text is fed into the Logistic Regression model, it goes through a feature extraction process using TF-IDF (Term Frequency-Inverse Document Frequency) vectorizers. It combines two types of features to understand the text better:

Word-level n-grams (combinations of 1-2 words).
Character-level n-grams (combinations of 3-5 characters).
This is a very solid, standard approach for text classification tasks like moderation or sentiment analysis!